# onnxruntime-node's postinstall downloads the CUDA EP binaries (~270MB) on
# linux — too large for the npm registry, and pure dead weight here: query
# embedding runs CPU-only (lib/embed-query.ts, dtype q8). Unskipped, they land
# inside bin/napi-v6/linux/x64/, the one directory next.config's
# outputFileTracingIncludes force-ships, ballooning the /companies function to
# ~406MB on Vercel/CI while darwin dev machines (no CUDA download) measure
# ~92MB — the discrepancy the function-size gate caught on 2026-07-17.
# The installer reads this via npm_config_onnxruntime_node_install
# (onnxruntime-node/script/install-utils.js).
onnxruntime-node-install=skip
